  "content": "# Background Worker — Decisions (March 2026)\n\n## Execution\nIn-process tokio::spawn task inside corvia serve. Default interval: 60 minutes. Configurable via forgetting.interval_minutes.\n\n## GC Cycle\n1. Load entries per scope (paginated, 1000/page)\n2. Compute retention_score, check inactivity policy, compare tier thresholds\n3. Apply transitions: Hot→Warm (tier field), Warm→Cold (+ HNSW orphan), Cold→Forgotten (+ discard embedding + archive)\n4. Single HNSW rebuild at end if any Warm→Cold transitions\n5. Apply budget policy if scope exceeds budget_top_n\n6. Emit metrics\n\n## Safeguards\n- Pinned: skip entirely\n- Auto-protected: can demote but not Forget\n- Rate limit: max 50 Forgotten transitions per cycle\n- Circuit breaker: abort if >50% Redb writes fail\n- Idempotent: crash-safe, next run re-evaluates all\n\n## v1 Constraints\nNo compaction, no LLM calls, no cross-scope analysis, no deletion. Purely deterministic.",
